Manchester United will be seeking revenge when they travel to face Wolves in the Premier League Monday night. Wolves won twice in three unbeaten encounters against the Red Devils last season. Ole Gunnar Solskjaer’s men began their campaign with a resounding 4-0 win over Chelsea. The kick-off is 8pm West African time. Monday, August 19
